Enum FileFunction.MaskType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<FileFunction.MaskType>
      • standardAttributes.FileFunction.MaskType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<FileFunction.MaskType>
    Enclosing class:
    FileFunction
    public static enum FileFunction.MaskType
extends java.lang.Enum<FileFunction.MaskType>
    An enumeration of known mask types: Soldermask, Carbonmask, Goldmask, Heatsinkmask, Peelablemask, Silvermask, Tinmask, and Unknown.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      Carbonmask
      A conductive paste used for specific purposes, often applied to pads for keypads, jumpers, or other similar applications.
      Goldmask
      A gold plating process to enhance electrical conductivity and corrosion resistance.
      Heatsinkmask
      A thermally conductive paste used to improve heat transfer.
      Peelablemask
      A temporary mask that is applied and then removed at a certain stage of the PCB assembly process.
      Silvermask
      A silver plating process to enhance electrical conductivity and corrosion resistance.
      Soldermask
      A polymer coating designed to prevent solder from adhering to specific areas of the PCB
      Tinmask
      A tin plating process to enhance electrical conductivity and corrosion resistance.
      Unknown
      This value is only used to indicate the Gerber file contains an invalid or unknown value.
